Her dancing was sensual and I have been told that my dancing is also in this aesthetic field', she claims.
The staging is based on two extraordinary collaborations: with Miguel Poveda, who will sing for Isabel again at one of their performances, as he did in `La puerta aberata'; and with Flamenco champion Matilde Coral, who wanted to work with one of her ex-students in exceptional cases.
`Matilde plays Tórtola, a very mature personality.
