Napolitano: "Prevention against accidents at work is crucial"
Every day in Italy 2500 accidents at work, three people die and 27 remain disabled for life.
For 2007, the data from Inail (Istituto nazionale contro gli infortuni sul lavoro) confirm that the fatal accidents at work were around 1200.
These figures illustrate the seriousness of a phenomenon which causes almost twice as many deaths as it is caused by murder.
Today, the Anmil (Associazione Nazionale Mutilati e Invalidi del Lavoro) in all the provinces of Italy will commit the 58th National Day for the Victims of Accidents to draw the attention of the social institutions and the media to this dramatic situation.
