"From the report – as stated in a note – it becomes clear that 5-10% of those who hear loud music with portable musical devices for at least five years per week risk the permanent loss of their hearing for at least one hour a day."
"I'm worried that a large number of young people, who usually put portable music devices and cell phones on a high volume, will damage their hearing without knowing it irreversibly," says Meglena Kuneva.
"From the scientific findings – that is to say, from the European Union – there is a clear risk that pushes for rapid action.
