When the study is examined in more detail, it turns out that in Milan a sleeping space in the district of Brianza is needed about 450 euros; a single room starts at 650 euros (in the district of Bande Nere) and ends with 800 euros in the neighborhood of Lambiate, Udine and Fiera or even 900 euros in the district of Vittoria.
In Florence a sleeping place costs an average of 350/400 euros, a room 700.
In Bologna, where the students concentrate around the university in the neighborhoods, 250/280 euros are for a sleeping place of nuts, 370 to 500 for a single room.
